## Memory & mechanisms

- `.ai_context/` is this project's persistent memory. `INDEX.md` + `state.md`
  are injected automatically at session start (`.claude/settings.json`
  hooks), including after compaction — no manual protocol needed.
- Run `/wrap` at the end of a session to write memory back.
- For instant lint feedback on every edit, copy
  `.claude/hooks/lint.sh.example` → `lint.sh` once the stack exists.

## Long-horizon tasks

- Any task expected to exceed ~30 minutes of autonomous work goes through
  `/task <description>` — milestone plan, a fresh executor context per
  milestone, adversarial verification, and a Stop gate on each milestone's
  verify command.
- Task work happens on a `task/<slug>` branch; every passed gate is a commit.
- Stuck-milestone escalation: retry differently → 3 divergent parallel
  attempts (worktrees) → reframe the problem → stop and report.
- `/task --auto <description>` runs unattended: ambiguity calls are
  recorded as `[ASSUMED: ...]` in spec.md instead of asked — review them
  before merging.
- Profile is auto-detected from the session model and frozen per task.
  To pin it for this project, uncomment one:
